flowRoot.flowPara: In Reinforcement Learning, an agent learns to iteract with an environment in order to maximize an overall reward. While this approach has been very successful, it doesn't work well with enviroments with sparse rewards.

Another limitation is that the reward is usually give by the environment, and not intrinsic to the agent. In the paper we reproduced, we try a new approach that pushes the agent towards exploration, without any external stimuli.
